<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <link href="/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" />
  <script src="/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>

  <!-- Include jQuery -->
  <script src="/jquery/dist/jquery.min.js"></script>

  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Potta+One&family=Raleway:ital,wght@0,100..900;1,100..900&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="stylesheets/style.css" />
</head>

<body>
  <!--NAVBAR-->
  <%- include('partials/navbar.ejs') %>

  <!--LANDING PAGE-->
  <section id="land" class="d-flex justify-content-center">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
          <div class="container">
            <div class="image-container">
              <img src="images/Group 21.png" alt="Image" class="img-fluid" />
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center unselectable">
            <h1 class="fw-bold display-1 mt-4 crave">Cravings</h1>
            <h1 class="fw-bold display-1 mt-4 satisfy">Satisfied</h1>
          </div>
          <h6 class="text-white mt-4 unselectable">
            Enjoy a variety of food choices at PUP-Lagoon without breaking the
            bank.
          </h6>
          <div class="mt-4">
            <h1 class="eat unselectable">
              <span style="color: #d23140">EAT</span>
              <span style="color: #fff6f6">Well</span>
            </h1>
            <h1 class="spend unselectable">
              <span style="color: #f1e423">SPEND</span>
              <span style="color: #fff6f6">Wisely</span>
            </h1>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4">
            <form action="/select" method="GET">
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-brand me-2">Get Started</button>
              <a href="#about" class="btn btn-brand ms-2">About</a>
            </form>
            
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!--MENU-->
  <section id="food-menu" class="menu-section user-select-none">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="menu-title">Food Categories</h2>
      <div class="menu-items">
        <div class="menu-item rice">
          <img src="images/Group 13.png" alt="Rice Meals" />
          <p class="rm">Rice Meals</p>
        </div>
        <div class="menu-item drinks">
          <img src="images/Group 14.png" alt="Beverages" />
          <p class="dr">Beverages</p>
        </div>
        <div class="menu-item snacks">
          <img src="images/Group 15.png" alt="Snacks" />
          <p class="sn">Snacks</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!--ABOUT-->
  <div id="about" class="about-section unselectable">
    <div class="row">
      <h2>About the Website</h2>
      <div class="col about-image">
        <img src="images/Group 23.png" alt="About Us" />
      </div>
      <div class="col about-text">
        <p>
          The PUP Lagoon Food Court offers a vibrant selection of delicious
          and budget-friendly meals to fuel your busy days at Polytechnic
          University of the Philippines. Whether you're craving Filipino
          favorites, refreshing snacks, or something in between, our diverse
          range of vendors caters to every taste and keeps your wallet happy.
          <br />
          <br />
          This website is a student project designed to help you explore the
          delicious and affordable food options at PUP Lagoon Food Court. It
          was created in partial fulfillment of the requirements for a Design
          and Analysis of Algorithms course.
          <br />
          <br />
          Our goal is to provide a user-friendly platform that leverages the
          power of algorithms to streamline your food selection experience at
          PUP Lagoon.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <!--Algorithm-->
  <div id="algorithm" class="algorithm-section unselectable">
    <h2>Algorithm</h2>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="algorithm-text">
          <h3>Knapsack Backtracking in Action:</h3>
          <p>
            Imagine a knapsack (a backpack) with limited space, representing
            your budget or dietary restrictions. The algorithm treats each
            food item as an object with a weight (price) and a value
            (satisfaction). The Knapsack Backtracking method explores all
            possible combinations of food items, aiming to fill your knapsack
            (maximize your satisfaction) while staying within your constraints
            (budget or restrictions).
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="algorithm-text">
          <h3>Constraint Propagation for Optimization:</h3>
          <p>
            To further optimize the search process, we incorporate Constraint
            Propagation. This technique identifies and eliminates irrelevant
            food combinations early on, focusing the search on options that
            meet your needs. By filtering out unsuitable choices, constraint
            propagation ensures the algorithm finds the most fitting
            combinations quickly and efficiently.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="algorithm-text">
          <h3>The Result: A Streamlined Food Selection Experience</h3>
          <p>
            Thanks to the Knapsack Backtracking algorithm and Constraint
            Propagation, our website can efficiently present you with a
            diverse range of food options that align with your preferences and
            budget. So, browse our menu with confidence, knowing that powerful
            algorithms are working behind the scenes to deliver a delightful
            dining experience.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <!--FOOTER-->
  <%- include('partials/footer.ejs') %>

  <script src="javascripts/main.js"></script>
</body>

</html>